article.description: Amarah Coleman and Kelly Campbell both hit four 3-pointers and scored 16 points and No. 17 DePaul rolled to a 107-46 win over Loyola-Chicago on Sunday, halting a two-game losing streak.
article.headline: No. 17 DePaul women bury Loyola-Chicago 107-46
article.story:
CHICAGO --  Amarah Coleman and Kelly Campbell both hit four 3-pointers and scored 16 points and No. 17 DePaul rolled to a 107-46 win over Loyola-Chicago on Sunday, halting a two-game losing streak.

Brooke Schulte and Jacqui Grant had 15 apiece for the Blue Demons (7-4) and fifth starter Jessica January added 12 with nine assists. Reserves Tanita Allen and Deja Cage had 11 points apiece and Lauren Prochaska had a career-high eight assists, matching Campbell and one less than January. Campbell had a career-best for points and assists.

In avenging last year's 88-75 loss -- which snapped a 21-game winning streak in the city series- DePaul had a season high in field goals (44), shooting percent (51.8), assists (35) and steals (17).

It was the most points allowed by the Ramblers since DePaul had 109 two years ago.

Kaitlyn Williams had 11 points for Loyola (1-9), which had 14 turnovers in the first quarter to fall behind 29-8. The Ramblers shot 29 percent and had 30 turnovers.
